'''KnownSafe''', Inc. was a [[cryptographic]] services company founded in April 2000 by [[Bruce Perens]], [[Len Sassaman]], and [[Rodney Thayer]]. The company aimed to provide novel cryptographic assurance capabilities to consumers based on privacy-preserving PKI techniques, but failed to secure necessary funding following the collapse of the [[Dot-com bubble]].

